          "_section": "The Amazon"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "4",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Lieutenant Colonel Percy Fawcett disappeared in this area of the jungle searching for the Lost City of Z. You search for any signs of the expedition or the legendary city (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You discover a young Kuikuro boy who requires convincing before he'll help you (). If you pass, he brings you to an ancient city where Fawcett has left behind his journal; gain 2 Clues. If you fail, the boy demands payment and disappears; discard 1 Item possession.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "2 Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              },
              {
                "text": "Item",
                "href": "/wiki/Item"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "A mosquito bite leaves you sick and feverish (-1). If you pass, you recover quickly, feeling better than before; discard 1 Illness or Injury Condition. If you fail, your symptoms grow worse; lose 1 Health and gain a Poisoned Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Illness",
                "href": "/wiki/Illness"
              },
              {
                "text": "Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Poisoned",
                "href": "/wiki/Poisoned"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Amazon"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Antarctica": {
      "tables": [
        {
          "ID #": "1",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Flying over the area, you see evidence of an ancient stone city.[1] You land your plane as close as you can and climb across the ice to reach the strange architecture ().",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "[1]",
                "href": "#cite_note-mountains_of_madness-1"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "The murals inside the city tell the story of the elder things. Retreat Doom by 1. However, your studies take a toll on your mind (). If you fail, you block everything you've learned from your mind; gain an Amnesia Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              },
              {
                "text": "Amnesia",
                "href": "/wiki/Amnesia"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "You fall through the ice into a stone chamber. Lose 1 Health and gain a Back Injury Condition. You search the dark chamber (-1). If you pass, you find the husk of an elder thing for study; retreat Doom by 1.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Back Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Back_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "Antarctica"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "2",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You hear a faint sound echoing up from the caves that lead down in to the darkness.[1] You listen carefully to discern the sound's origin ().",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "[1]",
                "href": "#cite_note-mountains_of_madness-1"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You identify the sound of shoggoths. You escape, but can barely keep yourself conscious waiting for a rescue (). If you pass, you spot something on the cave floor; gain 1 Artifact. If you fail, you pass out and hear the sounds of shoggoths everywhere you go; gain a Hallucinations Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              },
              {
                "text": "Hallucinations",
                "href": "/wiki/Hallucinations"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "\"Tekeli-li! Tekeli-li!\" You recognize it too late. The shoggoths overwhelm you (-1). If you pass, you overcome the threat; gain 2 Clues. If you fail, you escape by jumping off a ledge; gain a Leg Injury Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "2 Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              },
              {
                "text": "Leg Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Leg_Injury"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "Antarctica"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "3",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You find what you believe to be star-shaped burial mounds in the snow.[1] It is physically exhausting, but you try to dig the bodies out of the ice and snow ().",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "[1]",
                "href": "#cite_note-mountains_of_madness-1"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "An odd relic lies next to the creature's corpse. Gain 1 Artifact. Then you examine the body (-1). If you fail, you lose 1 Sanity staring too long to this alien horror.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Chipping through the ice, you slip and injure yourself. Gain a Leg Injury Condition. The rest of the expedition crew is too terrified to approach and you beg them for help (). If you pass, they spot something buried in the ice; gain 1 Artifact. If you fail, lose 2 Health as you crawl back to the camp.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Leg Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Leg_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "Antarctica"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "4",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "As you approach the dark tower, the landscape suddenly transforms around you, as if you were witnessing thousands of years passing in an instant.[2] The effect passes quickly but overwhelms your senses ().",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "[2]",
                "href": "#cite_note-beyond_mountain-2"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You realize that you've seen the future. In this vision, a being of unthinkable power escapes from this tower, unless you have the knowledge to prevent it (). If you pass, you restore the seals on the tower; retreat Doom by 1. If you fail, nothing can be done; lose 1 Sanity and gain a Paranoia Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              },
              {
                "text": "Paranoia",
                "href": "/wiki/Paranoia"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "You see your own severed head, connected to other heads by a strange, fibrous network. Lose 1 Sanity and gain a Hallucinations Condition. You hear many voices in your head, but one struggles to be heard over the others (-1). If you pass, this voice teaches you the arcane arts; gain 1 Spell.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Hallucinations",
                "href": "/wiki/Hallucinations"
              },
              {
                "text": "Spell",
                "href": "/wiki/Spell"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "Antarctica"
        }
      ]
    },
    "The Heart of Africa": {
      "tables": [
        {
          "ID #": "1",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "The whole jungle shakes, and the ground splits beneath your feet. You fall through the crevice into a vast subterranean tunnel ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You follow the tunnel to the ancient city of G'harne. Retreat Doom by 1. If you have read about G'harne, you know to leave quickly (). If you fail, you wake up in the jungle with no memory; gain an Amnesia Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              },
              {
                "text": "Amnesia",
                "href": "/wiki/Amnesia"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "You land painfully on your spine. Lose 1 Health and gain a Back Injury Condition. While you're stuck here, you examine this tunnel (-1). If you pass, you see that it was dug out by a large creature; retreat Doom by 1.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Back Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Back_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Heart of Africa"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "2",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "The old N'bangu man's map to the gray city of the white god relies on landmarks that are now overgrown by the dense jungle.[3] You search carefully to recognize anything familiar ().",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "[3]",
                "href": "#cite_note-jermyn-3"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You find the remains of a white ape and study the bones (). If you pass, you find a hastily drawn map that leads you to a hidden treasure; gain 1 Artifact. If you fail, something about this creature make you doubt your own humanity; gain a Hallucinations Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              },
              {
                "text": "Hallucinations",
                "href": "/wiki/Hallucinations"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Stumbling across a copper mine, you are immediately accused of being a thief or a saboteur. You fight to escape into the jungle (-1). If you pass, you find the gray city; gain 2 Clues. If you fail, gain a Detained Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "2 Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              },
              {
                "text": "Detained",
                "href": "/wiki/Detained"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Heart of Africa"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "3",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Suddenly, you are surrounded by leopard men! They quickly capture you, tie you up, and take you back to their village. On the way, you try to free yourself from the ropes that bind you ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "At their village, you spot a rare item sitting on an altar. Gain 1 Artifact. You escape and flee from the village as quickly as possible without watching where you are going (-1). If you fail, you collide with a statue of Tsathoggua; lose 1 Sanity.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Your escape attempt does more harm than good. Gain a Leg Injury Condition. You try to convince the leopard men that you are a messenger from their god (). If you pass, they let you go; gain 1 Artifact. If you fail, the leopard men attack you with primitive weapons as you escape; lose 2 Health.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Leg Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Leg_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Heart of Africa"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "4",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "In a part of the jungle avoided by all of the local tribes, you find a stone covered with strange dot patterns. You attempt to identify the origin of the shard and interpret the meaning of the patterns (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You identify it as a missing piece of the G'harne Fragments that leads you to a long-forgotten cave. Inside, you search through the ruins of an abandoned lair of elder things (-1). If you pass, you find a lost treasure; gain 1 Artifact.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Your failure hurts your reputation among your peers. Discard all Improvement tokens. Soon, a rival expedition tries to steal the fragment (). If you pass, you escape with the other expedition's notes; gain 2 Clues. If you fail, they leave you wounded; lose 2 Health.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "2 Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Heart of Africa"
        }
      ]
    },
    "The Himalayas": {
      "tables": [
        {
          "ID #": "1",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "A horrifying beast suddenly attacks you, almost as if it had stepped right out of your nightmares. Spawn a Monster on your space and immediately encounter it. If you defeat it, resolve the pass effect. If you do not defeat it, resolve the fail effect.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Monster",
                "href": "/wiki/Monster"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "The creature from your dreams is defeated; retreat Doom by 1. You look into local legends to find the link between this area and the Dreamlands (). If you fail, lose 2 Sanity as your uncertainty unhinges your mind.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Unable to overcome the threat, you run away and look for a place to hide (). If you pass, discard the Monster and retreat Doom by 1. If you fail, lose 1 Sanity as you cower in fear.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Himalayas"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "2",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You duck into a cave to find shelter from the deadly snowstorm. Inside, the tunnels twist and turn in the dark, making it almost impossible to navigate ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "Inside a well-lit laboratory, you find a human brain inside a cylinder. You can speak to the brain, but it disturbs you to do so (). If you pass, it tells you where the mi-go store their equipment; gain 1 Artifact. If you fail, you retreat from all human contact; gain a Paranoia Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              },
              {
                "text": "Paranoia",
                "href": "/wiki/Paranoia"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Large, winged, crab-like beings surround you. You're going to have to fight if you want to escape (-1). If you pass, you subdue the mi-go for study; gain 2 Clues. If you fail the creatures inject you with a glowing serum; gain an Internal Injury Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "2 Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              },
              {
                "text": "Internal Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Internal_Injury"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Himalayas"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "3",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "The gnoph-keh summons a terrible blizzard to destroy you and your expedition. You'll have to survive the storm before you can continue ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You weather the storm in a cave and find a statue of a three-eyed horror, surrounded by odd relics. Gain 1 Artifact. You try to determine the statue's origins (-1). If you fail, you do not recognize Rhan-Tegoth, and the icon remains a mystery that haunts your dreams; lose 2 Sanity.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Trapped by the storm, the other members of your expedition panic. You try to calm them (). If you pass, they are willing to continue, and you make a discovery; gain 1 Artifact. if you fail, their refusal fills you with doubts; gain a Paranoia Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              },
              {
                "text": "Paranoia",
                "href": "/wiki/Paranoia"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Himalayas"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "4",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "The Order of the Death's Head has arranged for a mass sacrifice of monks to call forth the Ogress of Ra-Sa.[4] You attack the Order's soldiers to free their prisoners. ().",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "[4]",
                "href": "#cite_note-deaths_head-4"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "The Order abandons the ritual, and you rescue the monks. One of them gratefully gives you a scroll that you attempt to interpret (-1). If you pass, you acquire arcane knowledge; gain 2 Spells. If you fail, the scroll's strange poetry bleeds into reality; gain a Hallucinations Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Spells",
                "href": "/wiki/Spells"
              },
              {
                "text": "Hallucinations",
                "href": "/wiki/Hallucinations"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "The fight leaves you wounded. Gain a Leg Injury Condition. The commander of the Order continues chanting, and the sound unnerves you (-1). If you pass, you steal the book he is reading from; gain 2 Clues. If you fail, the commander hexes you; gain a Cursed Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Leg Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Leg_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "2 Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              },
              {
                "text": "Cursed",
                "href": "/wiki/Cursed"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Himalayas"
        }
      ]
    },
    "The Pyramids": {
      "tables": [
        {
          "ID #": "1",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Bandits tie your hands and blindfold you. They lower you into catacombs deep under the pyramids and leave you there to die. You try to free yourself from your bonds ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You see now that you are in the Temple of the Sphinx. Retreat Doom by 1. You use your knowledge of Egyptology to find an exit (). If you fail, you wake up with no memory of how you escaped; gain an Amnesia Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              },
              {
                "text": "Amnesia",
                "href": "/wiki/Amnesia"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "While struggling with your bonds, you feel undead hands tearing at you. Lose 1 Health and gain an Internal Injury Condition. You gaze into the darkness (-1). If you pass, you identify mummies with the heads of animals; retreat Doom by 1.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Internal Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Internal_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Pyramids"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "2",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Inside the pyramid, you find a hidden passage leading to an undiscovered throne room. You explore the room for indications of its history ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You see a star map adjacent to a world map on the wall. You use the star map to determine a location on the world map (). If you pass, you discover a hidden cabinet built into the wall; gain 1 Artifact. If you fail, the maps remain a mystery; you lose 2 Sanity.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "As you search, Nephren-Ka appears! With a wave of his hand, you are overcome by pain (-1). If you pass, you crawl away; gain 2 Clues. If you fail, lose 1 Health and gain an Internal Injury Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "2 Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              },
              {
                "text": "Internal Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Internal_Injury"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Pyramids"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "3",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You reach for the ancient relic when a small white cat jumps in front of you. To your horror, the cat transforms into a demonic, feline creature and attacks ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "The demon shrivels down to a husk, leaving the relic unguarded. Gain 1 Artifact. Examining the item, you may be too distracted to notice the warning hieroglyph (-1). If you fail, you aren't prepared to evade the poisoned barb; lose 1 Health.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "The creature leaves you badly wounded. Gain a Leg Injury Condition. You cry out for help (). If you pass, the men who come to find you distract the beast, allowing you to procure the relic; gain 1 Artifact. If you fail, lose 2 Health as you have to walk without receiving medical attention.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Leg Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Leg_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Pyramids"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "4",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Once you reach Dashur, you begin digging through the rubble that had once been the White Pyramid, hoping to excavate the ancient burial chambers (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You uncover a vast labyrinth of underground tunnels. You only hope of navigating is to translate the hieroglyphs on the wall (). If you pass, you find your way to the royal treasury; gain 1 Artifact. If you fail, you slowly find your way back to the exit; become Delayed.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Artifact",
                "href": "/wiki/Artifact"
              },
              {
                "text": "Delayed",
                "href": "/wiki/Delayed"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "You exhaust yourself working into the night without result. Lose 1 Health. That night, a snake-eyed man dressed like a bedouin approaches you and offers you a deal. You may gain a Dark Pact to improve 1 skill of your choice.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Dark Pact",
                "href": "/wiki/Dark_Pact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Pyramids"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Tunguska": {
      "tables": [
        {
          "ID #": "1",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "A strange color that you've never seen before permeates the air. It crawls like a phosphorescent mist along every surface. You can feel its corrosive effect on your skin, and you struggle to escape the area ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "Behind you, the color flies up into space. You try to interpret what you've seen (). If you pass, you're sure the threat has passed; retreat Doom by 1. If you fail, your mind cannot accept what you've seen; gain an Amnesia Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              },
              {
                "text": "Amnesia",
                "href": "/wiki/Amnesia"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "The ground shakes and you are knocked off your feet. Lose 1 Health and gain a Leg Injury Condition. Gray dust fills the air, but you think you see a light (-1). If you pass, you see the color fly up into the air; retreat Doom by 1.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Leg Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Leg_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "Tunguska"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "2",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "A small piece of the stone you are standing on crumbles away, revealing a hollowed-out chamber beneath you. You look for a safe way to get inside ().",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
