    "The Key and the Gate": {
      "text": "The Key and the Gate are Special Encounters related to Yog-Sothoth. You are devoured. You are devoured. You are devoured. You are devoured. You are devoured. Discard all of your Clues, Spells, and Improvement tokens.",
      "tables": [
        {
          "ID #": "1",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "A mass of glowing spheres, mouths, and tentacles burst forth from the portal. You feel a terrible intelligence searching your mind for signs of corruption. If you have a Dark Pact Condition, you are devoured. The Lurker then fills your thoughts with forbidden knowledge (-1).",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Dark Pact",
                "href": "/wiki/Dark_Pact"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You exercise extreme mental discipline to regain control of your mind. By examining the images the Lurker has chosen to reveal, you believe that you can bind it between dimensions (). If you pass, you may discard 1 Spell to place 1 Eldritch token on the Ancient One sheet. If you fail or do not discard the Spell, lose 3 Sanity.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Spell",
                "href": "/wiki/Spell"
              },
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": "In one horrifying flash, your mind is flooded with knowledge of all places and all times as your molecules are torn apart. You are devoured.",
          "_section": "The Key and the Gate"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "2",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Yog-Sothoth's avatar 'Umr-At-Tawil, stands before the Ultimate Gate. He is a tall figure, wrapped in gray fabric, and you can hear his thoughts thundering in your head. He warns you to proceed no further if you are afraid (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "'Umr-At-Tawil guides you through the gates to encounter Yog-Sothoth (). You may spend any number of Clues to add 1 success to your test result for each Clue spent. If your test result is 3 or greater, you are allowed to return home; place 1 Eldritch token on the Ancient One sheet. Otherwise, Yog-Sothoth threatens to trap you on the doomed planet Yaddith; lose 3 Sanity.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              },
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": "'Umr-At-Tawil holds a large metallic sphere that radiates powerful pulses of energy. The rhythmic waves shake you to your core, tearing your body to pieces. You are devoured.",
          "_section": "The Key and the Gate"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "3",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Carl Sanford stands high atop a mountain in a swirling dimension of his own creation. He claims that the Silver Twilight Lodge has harnessed the power of Yog-Sothoth to transform him into a god. However, you suspect much of what you see is an illusion (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "Hoping to catch Sanford off guard, you lunge at him (). You may spend any number of Sanity to roll 1 additional die for each Sanity spent. If your test result is 3 or greater, you overpower him; place 1 Eldritch token on the Ancient One sheet. Otherwise, he manages to chant an incantation; gain a Cursed Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              },
              {
                "text": "Cursed",
                "href": "/wiki/Cursed"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": "You attempt to speak to Sanford, either to reason with him or to threaten him, but all that comes out of your mouth is a ritual chant, binding you to the Silver Twilight Lodge. You are devoured.",
          "_section": "The Key and the Gate"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "4",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You can sense Yog-Sothoth in your thoughts, trying to consume your identity by filling your memories with ultimate knowledge. You struggle against the swirling energy that drags you forward, into the gate (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "Rather than being consumed by knowledge, you repeat a chant that can allegedly purge a mind of all memories (). If you pass, you may gain an Amnesia Condition to place 1 Eldritch token on the Ancient One sheet. If you fail or do not gain the Condition, lose 3 Sanity.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Amnesia",
                "href": "/wiki/Amnesia"
              },
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": "You know the gate. You are the gate. You are the key and guardian of the gate. Past, present, future, all are one in you. You are devoured.",
          "_section": "The Key and the Gate"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "5",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Despite the reports of the mad albino woman's death, she stands at this gate to wait for her child, the so-called Dunwich Horror, to call its father's name. As soon as she sees you, she casts a hex, and you attempt to produce a protective ward (-1).[2]",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "[2]",
                "href": "#cite_note-lavinia-2"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "Your protective ward surprises her. You tell her that she's the last of the Whateley clan, hoping to intimidate her (). Roll 1 less die for each Cultist Monster on the game board (minimum 1 die). If you pass, place 1 Eldritch token on the Ancient One sheet. If you fail, she recognizes your deceit; advance Doom by 1.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Cultist",
                "href": "/wiki/Cultist"
              },
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              },
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "You know of no way to shield yourself from her powerful sorcery. Gain a Cursed Condition, a Madness Condition, and an Injury Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Cursed",
                "href": "/wiki/Cursed"
              },
              {
                "text": "Madness",
                "href": "/wiki/Madness"
              },
              {
                "text": "Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Injury"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Key and the Gate"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "6",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You see a circle of stones, each covered with magic runes. You sense that this is some sort of test of your knowledge (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You touch each rune in order, identifying yourself as a wizard. To your horror, you feel Yog-Sothoth taking over your mind, claiming you as its own (). Roll 1 less die for each Spell you have (minimum 1 die). If you pass, place 1 Eldritch token on the Ancient One sheet. If you fail, lose 3 Sanity.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Spell",
                "href": "/wiki/Spell"
              },
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Yog-Sothoth does not recognize you as a sorcerer and ejects you from the gate; gain 2 Spells and a Dark Pact Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Spells",
                "href": "/wiki/Spells"
              },
              {
                "text": "Dark Pact",
                "href": "/wiki/Dark_Pact"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Key and the Gate"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "7",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "The landscape around you changes constantly as Yog-Sothoth drags you through all worlds and all times. You search desperately for anything familiar to find your way home (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You sense your loved ones and mentally reach out to them for help (). Roll 1 less die for each investigator that has been defeated or devoured. If you pass, your body is snapped back to reality, place 1 Eldritch token on the Ancient One sheet. If you fail, you drift further through worlds beyond; gain a Lost in Time and Space Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              },
              {
                "text": "Lost in Time and Space",
                "href": "/wiki/Lost_in_Time_and_Space"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": "When your vision clears, you find yourself on a frozen plateau. No starts look down from the night sky. For a tragically brief time, you are the only living thing in the universe. You are devoured.",
          "_section": "The Key and the Gate"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "8",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You are surprised to discover the indistinct silhouette of a man on the other side of the gate. Without knowing his identity, you try to convince him to help you navigate these strange other worlds (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "He introduces himself as Randolph Carter and offers you his Silver Key. You try to harness its power (). You may gain a Dark Pact Condition to roll 3 additional dice. If your test result is 3 or greater, the key works; place 1 Eldritch token on the Ancient One sheet. Otherwise, you're hopelessly lost; gain a Lost in Time and Space Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Dark Pact",
                "href": "/wiki/Dark_Pact"
              },
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              },
              {
                "text": "Lost in Time and Space",
                "href": "/wiki/Lost_in_Time_and_Space"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "He introduces himself as the wizard Zkauba, and he uses his arcane powers to steal your experiences. Discard all of your Clues, Spells, and Improvement tokens.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Clues",
                "href": "/wiki/Clues"
              },
              {
                "text": "Spells",
                "href": "/wiki/Spells"
              },
              {
                "text": "Improvement",
                "href": "/wiki/Improvement"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Clue",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "The Key and the Gate"
        }
      ]
    },

    "R'lyeh Risen": {
      "text": "R'lyeh Risen are Special Encounters related to Cthulhu.",
      "tables": [
        {
          "ID #": "1",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "At the very peak of the island, you encounter a massive stone door featuring a horrific bas-relief of a dragon-like creature. Strange symbols are carved along the edge of the door. Some of the icons resemble drawings you've seen in books (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You spot a protective ward out of pace, hanging precariously. A member of your crew is on top of the door frame next to the ward. You warn him to carefully replace it (-1). If you pass, he does as you ask; place 1 Eldritch token on the active Mystery. If you fail, he fumbles it, resolve the fail effect.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              },
              {
                "text": "Mystery",
                "href": "/wiki/Mystery"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Influence",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Somewhere on the other side of the enormous door, you hear a thunderous splashing sound and feels the ground shake as something approaches the island's surface. Advance Doom by 1.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Doom",
                "href": "/wiki/Doom"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Doom",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "R'lyeh Risen"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "2",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "As you approach the uncharted island, you hear the sound of a cannon and feel the deck shudder. You ship is badly damaged, and if you hope to survive, you must overpower the crew aboard the gunship Alert, the source of the cannon fire (-1)",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "Once you have control of the ship, you find that it was filled with cultist devoted to Cthulhu. You search through their notes for information about the island (-1). If you pass, you find a folder with everything you need to know; place 1 Eldritch token on the active Mystery.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "The Alert's crew kill all of the sailors you were traveling with and knock you unconscious. When you wake up, you find yourself tied up in up in their makeshift brig. Gain a Detained Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Detained",
                "href": "/wiki/Detained"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "R'lyeh Risen"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "3",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You swim up to the slimy rocks and walk into the corpse city of R'lyeh. Inside, cyclopean, green, stone blocks meet at non-Euclidean angles. The very sight of this alien construction threatens to shatter your mind (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "Trying not to focus on the architecture, you instead take note of a series of hieroglyphics inscribed on the walls. You desperately try to interpret them for useful information ( -1). If you pass, place 1 Eldritch token on the active Mystery.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "Your life up until this moment has been a dream from which you are just awakening. You now understand that your true purpose is to offer yourself up as sacrifice to Cthulhu. Lose 3 Sanity.",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "R'lyeh Risen"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "4",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Enormous silhouettes of flying creatures descend from the clouds. The star spawn have arrived! They attack with blood-chilling ferocity (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You survive their onslaught and hide yourself in a small cavern. You wait there for reprieve, listening to the terrible alien shrieks of the creatures (-1). If you pass, they eventually relent; place 1 Eldritch token on the active Mystery. If you fail, the noise places horrible images into your mind; gain a Hallucinations Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              },
              {
                "text": "Mystery",
                "href": "/wiki/Mystery"
              },
              {
                "text": "Hallucinations",
                "href": "/wiki/Hallucinations"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Will",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "They crush you against the stones. You have no hope of standing up against their might; lose 3 Health.",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "R'lyeh Risen"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "5",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Hundreds of deep ones surface from the water, crawling up the green stones. You hide yourself and watch their priest perform a strange ritual (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "Although you cannot understand the words, the ritual reminds you of a similar ceremony performed by human cults (-1). If you pass, you recognize the moment when they will close their eyes and take the opportunity to escape; place 1 Eldritch token on the active Mystery. If you fail, you misinterpret the chant; resolve the fail effect.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "A loud croak informs you that one of the deep ones has spotted you. The monstrous fish creatures descend upon you from all sides. Lose 3 Health.",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Health",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "R'lyeh Risen"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "6",
          "Set": {
            "text": "01Core",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Core",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Horror"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "You recognize the alien landscape from a dream you've had. Lose 1 Sanity. You try to remember as many details as you can from the dream to navigate through the city (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Sanity",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Observation",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You make your way to a hidden chamber lined with strange glyphs carved into the stone. Some of the symbols seem familiar (-1). If you pass, you learn the story of how the elder things trapped Cthulhu in the city; place 1 Eldritch token on the active Mystery. If you fail, the images fester in your subconscious; gain a Paranoia Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              },
              {
                "text": "Mystery",
                "href": "/wiki/Mystery"
              },
              {
                "text": "Paranoia",
                "href": "/wiki/Paranoia"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "You quickly become lost and tumble down a long stone slope. Gain a Leg Injury Condition. As you climb to your feet you realize you're not alone. Spawn 1 Monster on your space.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Leg Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Leg_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Monster",
                "href": "/wiki/Monster"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "R'lyeh Risen"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "7",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "A swarm of elder things bursts out of the water and flies over the large stone outcroppings. One of the creatures takes notice of you. It swoops out of the sky and tries to entangle you in its tendrils (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Strength",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Pass Effect": {
            "text": "You keep the creature at bay, but several others have taken notice. You try to recall what you know of elder things (-1). If you pass, you know that they are enemies of Cthulhu, here to prevent his return, and you lie down and let them pass over you; place 1 Eldritch token on the active Mystery. If you fail, you run in a panic; resolve the fail effect.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "1 Eldritch token",
                "href": "/wiki/Eldritch_Token"
              },
              {
                "text": "Mystery",
                "href": "/wiki/Mystery"
              }
            ],
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Eldritch token",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Fail Effect": {
            "text": "You are lifted into the air and thrown to the ground; gain a Back Injury Condition, a Leg Injury Condition, and an Internal Injury Condition.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "Back Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Back_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Leg Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Leg_Injury"
              },
              {
                "text": "Internal Injury",
                "href": "/wiki/Internal_Injury"
              }
            ]
          },
          "_section": "R'lyeh Risen"
        },
        {
          "ID #": "8",
          "Set": {
            "text": "02Forsaken Lore",
            "images": [
              {
                "alt": "Forsaken Lore",
                "src": "data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D"
              }
            ]
          },
          "Initial Text": {
            "text": "Large tablets of black stone tower above you, each engraved with an R'lyehian, the blasphemous language of the star spawn (-1).",
            "images": [
              {
